course.subject: MATH
course.name: Combinatorics
course.description: Enumerative Combinatorics: bijective counting, permutation statistics, generating functions, partially ordered sets, Mobius inversions, Polya theory.  Graph Theory: cycle space, bond space, spanning-tree formulas, matching theory, chromatic polynomials, network flows.  Matroid Theory: matroid axioms, representations, duality, lattice of flats, transversals.
course.prerequisites: MATH 2343 or MATH 3343
